name: Halldóra Briem
content:
Halldóra Briem (13 February 1913, Vestmannaeyjar - 21 October 1993, Stockholm) was the first Icelandic woman to study architecture.[1] She studied architecture at the KTH Royal Institute of Technology in Stockholm, Sweden from 1935 to 1940.[2][3][4][5] She would go on to work professionally in Sweden.[5][2]

raw:
Halldóra Briem (13 February 1913, Vestmannaeyjar - 21 October 1993, Stockholm) was the first Icelandic woman to study architecture.[1] She studied architecture at the KTH Royal Institute of Technology in Stockholm, Sweden from 1935 to 1940.[2][3][4][5] She would go on to work professionally in Sweden.[5][2]
